<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,826,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
Length: male, 5.9–6.0 mm; female, 6.7–7.0 mm. Light greenish white species. Crown with anterior margin more narrowly pointed, lacks median apical black spot, two medium sized round spots each near lateral clypeal sutures that extending to ocelli, disk of crown with central elongate black spot. Pronotum without distinct central longitudinal brown line, with distinct punctures forming a transverse band separating pale anterior portion from dark posterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[540,628,976,1002]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–68" captionStartId="13.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,190,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-64@13.[166,1420,150,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–68. Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)., 60, head; 61, lateral view of aedeagus; 62, caudal view of aedeagus; 63, dorsal view of pygofer; 64, ventral view of subgenital plate; 65, male abdominal apodeme; 66, dorsal view of connective; 67, dorsal view of style; 68, female seventh sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133676/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). Clypellus and genae unmarked. Forewing often creamy white (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,211,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-50@2.[151,1436,197,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–2, Cofana bidentata n.sp., male &amp; female; 3, Cofana lineata (Distant); 4, Cofana nigrilinea (Stål); 5, Cofana spectra (Distant); 6, Cofana spiculata sp. nov.; 7, Cofana subvirescens (Stål); 8, Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133662/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). In some specimens, light greenish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,826,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[197,379,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer moderately produced with rounded caudo-dorsal margin and obliquely truncate caudal margin (
<figureCitation box="[336,425,1088,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–68" captionStartId="13.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,190,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-64@13.[166,1420,150,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–68. Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)., 60, head; 61, lateral view of aedeagus; 62, caudal view of aedeagus; 63, dorsal view of pygofer; 64, ventral view of subgenital plate; 65, male abdominal apodeme; 66, dorsal view of connective; 67, dorsal view of style; 68, female seventh sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133676/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Style in dorsal view short with distinct lateral lobe on shank, apical apophysis with denticles (
<figureCitation box="[273,363,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–68" captionStartId="13.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,190,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-64@13.[166,1420,150,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–68. Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)., 60, head; 61, lateral view of aedeagus; 62, caudal view of aedeagus; 63, dorsal view of pygofer; 64, ventral view of subgenital plate; 65, male abdominal apodeme; 66, dorsal view of connective; 67, dorsal view of style; 68, female seventh sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133676/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft slender, elongate with smooth dorsal and ventral margin; in caudal view uniformly broad throughout its length with round apex (
<figureCitation box="[842,987,1162,1188]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–68" captionStartId="13.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,190,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-64@13.[166,1420,150,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–68. Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)., 60, head; 61, lateral view of aedeagus; 62, caudal view of aedeagus; 63, dorsal view of pygofer; 64, ventral view of subgenital plate; 65, male abdominal apodeme; 66, dorsal view of connective; 67, dorsal view of style; 68, female seventh sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133676/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Figs 61, 62</figureCitation>
). Abdominal apodeme long, slender, extending beyond fourth segment (
<figureCitation box="[560,648,1200,1226]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–68" captionStartId="13.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,190,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-64@13.[166,1420,150,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–68. Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)., 60, head; 61, lateral view of aedeagus; 62, caudal view of aedeagus; 63, dorsal view of pygofer; 64, ventral view of subgenital plate; 65, male abdominal apodeme; 66, dorsal view of connective; 67, dorsal view of style; 68, female seventh sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133676/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,826,2018]" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[197,396,1237,1262]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Hind margin of seventh sternite convex medially produced with caudal margin truncate (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURES 60–68" captionStartId="13.[151,269,1843,1867]" captionTargetBox="[176,1407,190,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-64@13.[166,1420,150,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 60–68. Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)., 60, head; 61, lateral view of aedeagus; 62, caudal view of aedeagus; 63, dorsal view of pygofer; 64, ventral view of subgenital plate; 65, male abdominal apodeme; 66, dorsal view of connective; 67, dorsal view of style; 68, female seventh sternite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133676/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="47">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
